    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's a really weird sound though. like a buzzing or a constant hum that just won't stop when it's trying to kick on. almost sounds like something is vibrating inside. could it be a bad part or is it just a weird electrical glitch?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That buzzing or vibrating sound while trying to kick on is almost certainly a bad part, likely a failing start capacitor or a seized compressor motor, rather than a simple electrical glitch. When the capacitor fails, it can't provide the initial surge of power needed to spin the motor, causing the hum and vibration you're hearing. It's not just a glitch; the capacitor is literally the weak link holding the whole system together, and if it pops, it could leave you with a dead unit. You should definitely call a pro to replace it, as dealing with high-voltage capacitors without the right tools is risky and could lead to electric shock or further damage.",
